          <updateDate>2017-06-07T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Helping Overcome Trauma for Children Alone in Rear Seats Act or the HOT CARS Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation to issue a final rule to require that all new passenger motor vehicles weighing less than 10,000 pounds be equipped with a system for rear seating positions to alert (by an auditory and visual alert that may be combined with a haptic alert) the motor vehicle operator to check rear designated seating positions after the vehicle motor is deactivated.</p> <p>A state shall use a portion of its highway safety program funds to educate the public on the risks of leaving a child or unattended passenger in a vehicle after the vehicle motor is deactivated. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
